704820f-a.title: Brooklyn: Henry Street - Middagh Street
704820f-a.text:
Henry Street, at the N.E. corner of Middagh Street, showing a 2-story
building, used at various intervals as a meat market, and as a central dis-
tributing point fer ice.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.

704821f-a.title: Brooklyn: Henry Street - Middagh Street
704821f-a.text:
34 Henry Street, west side, between Middagh and Cranberry Streets.
A view of an antique shop, in an old frame building.
February 5, 1931.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

705714f-a.title: Brooklyn: Middagh Street - Henry Street
705714f-a.text:
Middagh Street, west of Henry Street, showing in the foreground, the
Assumption Parochial School, under the Jurisdietion of the parish by that
name, with the rectory on the south side ot the street, and farther westward.
I the background, appear sky-scrapers of lower Manhattan.
April 16, 1936.
P. L. 3perr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.

704819f-a.title: Brooklyn: Henry Street - Middagh Street
704819f-a.text:
Henry Street, at the N.W. corner of Middagh Street, showing Macon Au and
Magenheimer Candy Co., manufacturers of Mason's ''Peaks'', a candy confection.
April 1, 1937.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
